    A multipack of 121212 cans of Ned's cola cost £6.95\pounds 6.95£6.95.

    A single can of Ned's cola costs 65 pence65 \ \text{pence}65 pence if bought individually.

    Calculate how much cheaper it is to buy a multipack of 121212 cans than to buy 121212 cans individually, giving your answer in pence.

    As per the question,

    Cost of multipack of 121212 cans of Ned's cola =£6.95= \pounds 6.95=£6.95

    Cost of single can =65pence=65 \text {pence}=65pence

    Cost of 121212 cans if it bought individually =12×65pence= 12 \times 65 \text {pence}=12×65pence

    =12×65=780pence\begin{aligned} &= 12 \times 65 \\\\ &= 780 \text {pence} \end{aligned}​=12×65=780pence​

    Now convert the pounds into pence.

    £1=100pence£6.95=100×6.95=695pence\begin{aligned} \pounds 1 &= 100 \text {pence} \\\\ \pounds 6.95 &= 100 \times 6.95 \\\\ &= 695 \text {pence} \end{aligned}£1£6.95​=100pence=100×6.95=695pence​

    =780−695=85pence\begin{aligned} &= 780 - 695 \\\\ &= 85 \text {pence} \end{aligned}​=780−695=85pence​

    it is 85pence85 \text{pence}85pence cheaper to buy a multipack of 121212 cans than to buy 121212 cans individually.
